# API conventions

## Structure

- Routes under `src/app/api/events/` per `docs/design.md` §6
- Validate all inputs with Zod schemas from `src/lib/schemas.ts`
- Use Prisma client from `src/lib/db.ts`

## Authorization

| Route | Credential |
|-------|------------|
| Guest read/respond | `eventId` in path |
| Host read/update | `hostToken` query or header |
| Guest update | `responseToken` in path |

Return `404` for bad `eventId` or `hostToken`. Return `403` when token is valid format but not allowed (e.g. guest write after deadline).

## Tokens

- `eventId`: nanoid, length ≥ 21
- `hostToken`: nanoid, length ≥ 32
- `responseToken`: generated on response create; unique per response

## Data rules

- Slots: `type` is `date` | `datetime`; `startAt` stored in JST semantics
- Deleting a slot cascades deletes on related `Answer` rows
- `PATCH` events: allow title, description, deadline, slot add/remove

## Responses

- Use consistent JSON shape; include `{ error: string }` on failure
- Appropriate status codes: 400 validation, 403 forbidden, 404 not found, 201 created
